I couldn't get past an error when I set up a &quot;relation&quot; between two tables and tried to see a PDF graphic of the relation. The sql call to the relation kept retrieving 0 records. Soooo.
I modified the following in pdf_schema.php and then all was fine.
Original code: $sql = 'SELECT *' . ' FROM ' . PMA_backquote($cfgRelation['relation']) . ' WHERE master_db = \'' . $db . '\' ' . ' AND foreign_db = \'' . $db . '\' ' . ' AND master_table IN (' . $intable .')'; . ' AND foreign_table IN (' . $intable .')';
New Code $sql = 'SELECT *' . ' FROM ' . PMA_backquote($cfgRelation['relation']) . ' WHERE master_db = \'' . $db . '\' ' . ' AND master_table IN (' . $intable .')';
In my experience a table having a relation unto itself is rather rare. Mostly you have table external relations.

