if you calculate the width of the table with the 
longest name. 
here is a function to get the lenth of a string without 
using GDlib: 
function pixellen($str){ // gets the approximate length 
of a string in pixel 
    // it is calculated for the font arial and fontsize 
12,  
    // but it works as a measurement for all sizes and 
most fonts have similar proportions 
    $b[1]="ilI:;,.!'"; 
    $b[2]="j[]"; 
    $b[3]='frt-"/(){}1 '; 
    $b[4]="kJ"; 
    $b[5]="abcdeghnopqsuvxyzEFLPT$=?+234567890"; 
    $b[6]="BCDHKNRSUXZ_&"; 
    $b[7]="mAGMOQVY"; 
    $b[8]=""; 
    $b[9]="w%"; 
    $b[10]=""; 
    $b[11]="W"; 
    for($i=0; $i<strlen($str); $i++):      // for each 
letter 
        $found=0; 
        for($j=1; $j<=11; $j++): 
            if ( strstr($b[$j], $str[$i])) 
$pixel=$pixel+$j; 
            $found=1; 
            continue; 
        endfor; 
        if ($found==0)  $pixel+=5; // all other characters 
    endfor; 
    # change the factor to fit your font or just use 
the result as a measure 
    $factor=1.5; 
    return ($pixel*$factor); 
}

