When exporting to a SQL query phpMyAdmin will break functions into multiple columns. It will then remove the same ammount of columns passed to the funciton from the end of the column list.
ex: SELECT CONCAT( 'DOMAIN\\' , `username` ) AS 'uname', 'fullname';
will export a query: INSERT INTO table ( `DOMAIN\\`, `username`) VALUES ( 'DOMAIN\\john', 'John Doe' ); instead of ...table (`uname`,`fullname`) values...
Similarly, phpMyAdmin doesnt recognise renamed columns in the export: select `name` as 'fullname' where 1; will export: insert into table ('name') values ('John Doe');

