Using session_cache_limiter('private') could provoke some display bug because it set a max-age=(session.cache_expire in the future) 
Despite the Expires date to 1981, Firefox sometimes doesn't reload the page. 

For example, modifing config.inc.php with a lot of servers could become hell. 

I invite you to use "nocache" or remove the use of session_cache_limiter at least while the user is not logued. 

Details :  
File : libs/session.inc.php 
Line : ~57 

// some pages (e.g. stylesheet) may be cached on clients, but not in shared 
// proxy servers 
session_cache_limiter('private');

