Sometimes tables get that red &quot;Overhead&quot; word near Space Usage  
informations. 

  Browsing table by table looking for overheaded  
tables is annoying. A little snippet could be added to optimize all  
tables: 

$tables =  
mysql_list_tables('database_name'); 

while  
(list($table_name) = mysql_fetch_array($tables)) { 
    $sql =  
&quot;OPTIMIZE TABLE $table_name&quot;; 
    mysql_query($sql) or  
exit(mysql_error()); 
}

It would be nice if the SQL parser would recognize "CREATE TRIGGER" sql statements and just change DELIMITER for this single statement to something not used in the statement, i.e. "//".
Example query:
CREATE TRIGGER trigger_documents_forum_delete AFTER DELETE ON documents FOR EACH ROW BEGIN IF OLD.document_category_id=2 THEN UPDATE forum_postings SET last_update=NOW() WHERE node_id=OLD.foreign_id; END IF; END;
phpMyAdmin should execute automatically before a "CREATE TRIGGER" statement:
DELIMITER //
and after the "CREATE TRIGGER" statement:
// DELIMITER ;
Conclusion: Each single "CREATE TRIGGER" statement should be surrounded automatically by two DELIMITER statements. The working example from the MySQL 5.0.11 command line is:
DELIMITER // CREATE TRIGGER trigger_documents_forum_delete AFTER DELETE ON documents FOR EACH ROW BEGIN IF OLD.document_category_id=2 THEN UPDATE forum_postings SET last_update=NOW() WHERE node_id=OLD.foreign_id; END IF; END;// DELIMITER ;
GUI support for triggers could be added later of course ;)
Best regards, Ren Leonhardt

Hi. 
I needed to hide more than one database with phpmyadmin. So I try to replace the value $cfg['Servers'][$i]['hide_db'] = '' by an array, then by db names separated by commas.  

By checking the sources, this features is not implemented (yet hehe). 

The modification is easy to do, just one function in librairies/List_DataBase.class.php . Here is the code (I just added the part "if is_array()") : 

[code] 
	function _checkHideDatabase() 
	{ 
		if (empty($GLOBALS['cfg']['Server']['hide_db'])) { 
			return; 
		} 
		foreach ($this->items as $key => $db) { 
			if(is_array($GLOBALS['cfg']['Server']['hide_db'])){ 
				foreach($GLOBALS['cfg']['Server']['hide_db'] as $hide){ 
					if (preg_match('/' . $hide . '/', $db)) { 
						unset($this->items[$key]); 
						break; 
					} 
				} 
			} 
			else{ 
				if (preg_match('/' . $GLOBALS['cfg']['Server']['hide_db'] . '/', $db)) { 
					unset($this->items[$key]); 
				} 
			} 
		} 
		// re-index values 
		$this->_need_to_reindex = true; 
	} 
[/code]

